import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['price'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['mileage'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='mileage', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['mileage'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of car mileage?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="body-style", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of car body styles?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data['mpg'] = pd.to_numeric(data['mpg'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='price', y='mpg', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between car price and fuel efficiency?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
